description: Double for Manny Duku as Solihull Moors beat Ebbsfleet United in the National League
title: Solihull Moors 2-1 Ebbsfleet United
title_page: Solihull Moors 2-1 Ebbsfleet United: National League - BBC Sport
maintext:
Manny Duku marked his full Solihull debut with a brace as they registered their first National League win this year by beating bottom-of-the-table Ebbsfleet at Damson Park.
The 32-year-old forward this week signed a short-term deal with the club after leaving Hednesford and netted two minutes before half-time, heading in a cross from James Clarke.
Ebbsfleet, now without a win in 28 games dating back to mid-September, levelled nine minutes into first-half stoppage time when substitute Kwame Thomas converted a penalty after Alex Lankshear was brought down.
Toby Edser was sent off for Ebbsfleet for a second yellow card six minutes after the break and Duku made them pay five minutes from time as Solihull ended a run of 10 games without a win.
